- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of computing nested fixpoints. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with parity games, which are a topic in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the computation of fixpoints of set-valued functions, which can be relevant in programming language semantics.
